<item>
            <title>[NET-704] NTPUDPClient does not check response packet pairing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-704</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;NTPUDPClient does not check the originate time of response to match the transmit time of request. If the transmit time does not matches the originate time, then the computed time information is invalid. This may happen in case of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;invalid server implementation,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;on packet lost/duplication if NTPUDPClient instance is used for multiple requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Fix is easy, getTime method could throw IOException in case of no match. Patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/92&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/92&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
